{
  "text": "However, PnCs comprised of pillar arrays suffer from a number of disadvantages. In particular, as the pillars obtrude from a surface they are structurally fragile and also, in contrast to non-resonant holes, or the recently demonstrated monolithic phonon-polarition induced PnCs 26 , they are not compatible with the integration of other layers on the surface. For example, there is growing interest in the integration of SAW devices with 2D materials such as graphene and molybdenum disulphide [CITATION_1] 28 .",
